<#
.SYNOPSIS
  WimWizard-GUI.ps1 - Graphical launcher for WimWizard.ps1

.DESCRIPTION
  Windows Forms GUI that lets you select languages, choose which Appx packages
  to remove, configure options, and launch WimWizard.ps1 in a new PowerShell
  console window with the selected parameters.

  Must be placed in the same folder as WimWizard.ps1.

.NOTES
  Author  : Mathias Haas, Fidelity Consulting
  Contact : bWF0aGlhcy5oYWFzQGZpZGVsaXR5Y29uc3VsdGluZy5zZQ== (base64)
  License : GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)
            https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html
  Version : 2.2.1
  Product : WIM Wizard (tribute to WIM Witch by Donna Ryan)
  Requires: Windows PowerShell 5.1+

  CHANGELOG
  2.2.1  Renamed 'en' language entry to 'gb' (English British). Now injects
         only en-GB instead of en-GB + en-US. en-US is always present as the
         base image fallback and does not need to be injected. Filename preview
         now shows 'gb' instead of 'en' for British English builds.
  2.2.0  Added LTSC 2024 ISO detection: ISO name pattern extended to match
         SW_DVD9_WIN_ENT_LTSC_2024_* in Update-ISOStatus and Update-ArchPanel.
         ISO probe now detects edition from filename (LTSC2024 vs 25H2) and
         returns a BUILD|EDITION token. $Script:EditionTag set accordingly.
         Get-FilenamePreview uses EditionTag instead of hardcoded '25H2', so
         LTSC builds produce Win11_LTSC2024_* output filenames. Help tab updated
         with LTSC 2024 ISO filename examples.
  2.1.1  Fixed Run button not appearing when source folder path is typed manually
         (TextChanged now triggers Start-ISOProbe instead of Update-ISOStatus).
         Also fixes Run button staying visible/green after changing to a path
         without a valid Windows ISO - probe immediately hides button and
         re-evaluates correctly on completion.
  2.1 beta Skip Languages now greys out all language checkboxes so it is clear
           no languages will be installed. Unchecking restores the previously
           saved selections from the registry. Language checkboxes are also
           restored on startup if SkipLPs was persisted as checked.
  2.0 beta Blue ribbon now shows "WIM WIZARD v<script> / GUI v<gui>" with
           script version read dynamically from WimWizard.ps1 at startup.
           GUI version bumped to 2.0 beta alongside main script 5.0 beta.
  1.9.4  Fixed FoD dirty-detection: Get-SettingsSnapshot now includes FoD
         checkbox state. Previously, ticking a FoD never marked settings as
         changed, so the "Save settings?" prompt on close was never triggered.
  1.9.3  FoD selections now persisted to registry (Save-Settings/Load-Settings).
         Selected FoD keys saved as comma-separated string under "FoDs" value.
         Loaded on startup and restored to checkboxes like Languages and Apps.
  1.9.2  Fixed Appx null-bug: when all apps are unchecked, the GUI now passes
         -SkipAppxRemoval instead of an empty -AppxListPath XML. The empty XML
         caused a null-pipeline issue in the parser that fell through to the
         full default removal list regardless of user selection.
  1.9.1  Features on Demand tab (between Options and Help). Supports .NET 3.5
         and RSAT tools (AD, Group Policy, Server Manager). RSAT items hidden
         when ARM64 is selected (not supported on ARM64).
  1.9.0  ARM64 support: detects x64 and arm64 Windows and LP ISOs separately.
         Architecture radio toggle shown when both Windows ISOs present.
         LP ISO indicator validates correct arch LP ISO for selected build.
         Elevation warning shown if GUI not running as Administrator.
         Filename preview updates with _arm64 suffix for ARM64 builds.
  1.8.0  Added zh-HK (Chinese Hong Kong) to language list. Fixed Japanese
         code: GUI uses 'ja', main script now accepts both 'ja' and 'jp'.
  1.7.0  Run button hidden until Windows ISO found and build string resolved.
         Completion screen hides bottom bar (run button + command preview).
         Time estimates updated from real build log (~60 min for 4 langs).
  1.6.0  ISO status indicators below source folder showing green checkmark
         or red X for Windows ISO and Language Pack ISO. Indicators update
         live as source folder changes and hide in patch mode. Run validates
         required ISOs and warns if missing. Expanded app list to 36 apps
         synced with main script defaults. Filename probe extracts build
         from ISO name first (instant) before falling back to mount (~10s).
  1.5.0  Registry save/load for all settings. Auto-save on Run, ask on exit.
         Nordic defaults removed (settings persisted). ISO probed at startup
         for real build string. GUI minimizes on run, restores with completion
         screen. Tribute removed from blue bar. Icon moved 5px left. Help
         corrected.
  1.4.0  Patch mode now bumps date in output filename. Added Help tab with
         full usage instructions, setup guide, monthly patching workflow,
         standalone usage and file reference.
  1.3.1  Run button replaced with custom image (PictureBox with hand cursor
         and subtle hover highlight).
  1.3.0  Patch mode: "Patch existing image" toggle in Options tab. Browses for
         existing WIM, reads installed languages via Get-WindowsImage and pre-
         checks matching language boxes. Languages and Applications tabs grey
         out in patch mode. Passes -PatchExistingWim to WimWizard.ps1.
  1.2.0  GUI always passes -Unattended to WimWizard.ps1 - all choices made
         in the GUI so no interactive prompts appear in the console.
         Removed redundant "Unattended mode" checkbox from Options tab.
         Run button uses temp launcher script (-File) instead of -Command
         to avoid argument quoting issues with languages and paths.
         Removed #Requires -RunAsAdministrator (only main script needs it).
         Languages value quoted correctly to survive PowerShell arg parsing.
         OutputPath always included in command preview from first render.
  1.1.0  Removed alias language entries, sorted by display name (39 languages).
         Verified Appx list against Microsoft official 25H2 provisioned app policy.
         Embedded wiz.ico as base64 - no separate icon file needed.
         Added "Check defaults" button to Applications tab.
         Quick Assist, Store Music, Store Video added as default removals.
         Bottom bar layout: equal margins, command text aligned to button.
         Form height reduced from 720 to 620px.
  1.0.0  Initial release. Languages, Applications, Options tabs. Dark theme.
         Live filename preview updates on language selection. XML Appx export.
         Launches WimWizard.ps1 in new elevated PowerShell window.
#>

