$HelpText.Text = @"
WIM WIZARD - Quick Start Guide
===============================

WIM Wizard services a Windows 11 Enterprise WIM image for deployment via
SCCM/MECM. It injects language packs, removes unwanted apps, and applies
the latest Patch Tuesday updates - all in one automated process.

You need ISOs from Microsoft Volume Licensing. See links below.
  x64 build (25H2 Enterprise):
    - Windows 11 Enterprise ISO  (SW_DVD9_Win_Pro_11_25H2_64BIT_*.ISO)
    - Language Pack ISO (x64)    (SW_DVD9_Win_11_*_x64_*_LangPack_*.ISO)
  x64 build (LTSC 2024):
    - Windows 11 Enterprise ISO  (SW_DVD9_WIN_ENT_LTSC_2024_64-bit_*.ISO)
    - Language Pack ISO (x64)    (SW_DVD9_Win_11_*_x64_*_LangPack_*.ISO)
  ARM64 build:
    - Windows 11 Enterprise ISO  (SW_DVD9_Win_Pro_11_25H2*Arm64_*.ISO)
    - Language Pack ISO (ARM64)  (SW_DVD9_Win_11_*_Arm64_*_LangPack_*.ISO)

Place all needed ISOs in the same folder (ISO-Source\ next to the script).
You can have all four ISOs present at once - the correct ones are selected
automatically based on the chosen architecture.


TAB: LANGUAGES
--------------
Select which language packs to inject. Previously saved selections are
restored automatically from the registry on startup.

The output filename preview at the bottom updates live as you select
languages - e.g. Win11_25H2_26200.xxxx_da_fi_no_se_20260404.wim


TAB: APPLICATIONS
-----------------
Choose which built-in apps to remove from the image. Apps checked by
default are common corporate removals (Xbox, Clipchamp, Outlook etc.).

Apps not checked by default (Calculator, Camera, Notepad etc.) are kept
in the image since they are generally useful in a work environment.

  Check all      - Mark all apps for removal
  Uncheck all    - Keep all apps
  Check defaults - Reset to the recommended default selection


TAB: OPTIONS
------------
Source folder:     Folder containing the ISO files.
                   (Windows ISO + matching LP ISO for your target arch).
                   Default: ISO-Source\ next to WimWizard.ps1

Output WIM:        Where to save the finished WIM. Auto-generated
                   from version, languages and date if left blank.

Skip updates:      Do not download or apply Patch Tuesday updates.
Skip lang packs:   Build English-only image (no LP injection).
Skip Appx removal: Keep all built-in apps.
Patch existing image:
  Instead of building from the ISO, patch an already-serviced WIM with
  the latest updates only. Language packs and app removal are skipped.
  The output filename keeps the source name with today's date.
  Use this for monthly patch cycles after the initial build.


TAB: FEATURES ON DEMAND
------------------------
Optional Windows features installed into the WIM from the LP ISO.
No separate download is required - the LP ISO contains all FoD packages.

  .NET Framework 3.5  Required by many legacy enterprise applications.
                      Supported on both x64 and ARM64.

  RSAT: Active Directory, Group Policy, Server Manager
                      Remote Server Administration Tools for IT admins.
                      x64 only - not available for ARM64 offline builds.

RSAT checkboxes are automatically hidden when ARM64 architecture is
detected (only one Windows ISO in source folder, ARM64 type).


FIRST-TIME SETUP
----------------
1. Download the Windows 11 Enterprise ISO and Language Pack ISO from:
   https://admin.microsoft.com -> Downloads & Keys -> Windows 11 Enterprise

2. Place both ISOs in the ISO-Source\ folder next to WimWizard.ps1, e.g.:
   C:\WimWizard\ISO-Source\

3. Run WimWizard-GUI.ps1 as Administrator (right-click -> Run with PowerShell)

4. Select your languages, review app removal, click Run.

5. Import the finished WIM into SCCM:
   Software Library -> OS Images -> right-click -> Update Distribution Points


MONTHLY PATCHING
----------------
1. Check "Patch existing image" in the Options tab.
2. Browse to your last built WIM (e.g. in Output\).
3. Languages are read automatically from the WIM.
4. Click Run - only updates are downloaded and applied.
5. Output filename is the same as the source but with today's date.


STANDALONE (NO GUI)
-------------------
Full build:
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -Languages "da,fi,no,se" -Unattended

ARM64 build:
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -ARM64 -Languages "da,fi,no,se" -Unattended
  (ARM64 FoD note: only -FoDList "NetFx3" is supported; RSAT is x64 only)

With Features on Demand:
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -Languages "da,fi,no,se" -FoDList "NetFx3,RsatAD" -Unattended

With manually downloaded updates (skip auto-download):
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -Languages "da,fi,no,se" -UpdatePath "C:\Updates\" -Unattended

Patch existing:
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -PatchExistingWim "Output\Win11_25H2_..._20260310.wim" -Unattended

Custom app list (generated by GUI):
  .\WimWizard.ps1 -Languages "se" -AppxListPath "WimWizard-AppxList.xml" -Unattended


FILES
-----
  WimWizard.ps1           Main servicing script
  WimWizard-GUI.ps1       This graphical launcher
  WimWizard-AppxList.xml  Custom app removal list (generated on Run)
  ISO-Source\             Place Windows ISO and LP ISO here
  Updates\                Cached update files (reused on next run)
  Output\                 Default output folder for finished WIMs
  Output\WIMServicing_*.log  Build log for each run


VERSION
-------
  WIM Wizard GUI  v$WimWizardVersion
  WIM Wizard      v$ScriptVer

  A tribute to WIM Witch by Donna Ryan
  Developed by Mathias Haas for Fidelity Consulting
"@
